## 🌈 Introduction to Colors

Colors on computers are made by mixing three colors:

* ❤️ Red
* 💚 Green
* 💙 Blue

That's why it's called RGB!

## 🎨 Your First Color

Let's create something with color using Kino:

```elixir
# Red text
Kino.Markdown.new("# 🔴 This text is special!") |> Kino.render()

# Large text
Kino.Markdown.new("## This is smaller") |> Kino.render()

# Normal text
Kino.Markdown.new("This is normal text with emojis 🌟") |> Kino.render()
```

## 🌟 HTML Colors

We can use special colors with HTML:

```elixir
Kino.Markdown.new("""
<p style="color: red; font-size: 24px;">RED Text! ❤️</p>
<p style="color: blue; font-size: 24px;">BLUE Text! 💙</p>
<p style="color: green; font-size: 24px;">GREEN Text! 💚</p>
""")
```

